## Gaussian Splat Viewer

### Component: `src/components/specimen-splat-viewer.tsx` (~320 lines)

Library: `@mkkellogg/gaussian-splats-3d` v0.4.7

**Features:**
- Auto-rotate (0.5 RPM, stops on user interaction)
- Camera presets: Front, Side, Top, 3/4 view
- Interactive drag-to-rotate + wheel-to-zoom
- Share button (copy URL or native share)
- Loading state with fallback image
- Responsive 4:3 aspect ratio

**Props:**
```typescript
interface SpecimenSplatViewerProps {
  splatUrl: string                    // KSPLAT file URL
  initialCamera?: SplatCamera         // Custom starting viewpoint
  presets?: CameraPreset[]            // Custom preset buttons
  fallbackImage?: string              // Fallback JPG during load
  className?: string
}
```

**Default camera presets:**
```typescript
[
  { label: "Front", position: [0, 0, 3], lookAt: [0, 0, 0] },
  { label: "Side", position: [3, 0, 0], lookAt: [0, 0, 0] },
  { label: "Top", position: [0, 3, 0.1], lookAt: [0, 0, 0] },
  { label: "3/4", position: [2, 1.5, 2], lookAt: [0, 0, 0] },
]
```

**File format:** KSPLAT (binary compressed Gaussian Splat)
**CDN:** `fh3asutxdchzzmhw.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/borussia-splats/`

---

## Gaussian Splatting Pipeline (Outside Repo)

### Overview
Photographs -> COLMAP SfM -> OpenSplat training -> PLY -> KSPLAT -> Vercel Blob

### Capture Protocol (LOCKED)
- Turntable + iPhone on tripod
- 3 heights (15deg, 45deg, 70deg) x 12 positions (30deg increments) = 36 shots
- Black velvet background (eliminates COLMAP confusion)
- AE/AF locked, ProRAW optional
- Quality gate: COLMAP exhaustive matcher on-site; >=80% registration = proceed

### Pipeline Directories
```
~/splat-projects/
  specimens/{id}/                   # Per-specimen data
    capture/                        # Original photos/video
    colmap_ws/                      # COLMAP workspace
    runs/
      {date}-{iters}-{node}/        # Training runs
        output.ply                  # Final model
        opensplat.log               # Training log
        params.json                 # Flags, node, date
        scores.json                 # Grade, quality metrics
        renders/                    # Validation renders
  tools/                            # Pipeline scripts (30+)
    run-colmap.sh                   # COLMAP launcher
    run-splat.sh                    # OpenSplat launcher (canonical)
    score-splat.py                  # Quality grading (A/B/C/D/F)
    deploy-splat.sh                 # PLY -> Vercel Blob (Director-gated)
    preflight.sh                    # Pre-training checks
    assess-images.py                # Image quality auditor
    make-colmap-masks.py            # Background removal masks
  completed-plys/                   # Archive (~2.5GB, 20 files)
```

### SfM Methods
- **COLMAP** (primary): SIFT features, exhaustive matcher <=60 imgs, sequential >60
- **DUSt3R** (experimental): Transformer-based depth, metric scale recovery
- **MASt3R** (planned): Asymmetric stereo transformer, 2.4x faster

### Training Tiers
| Tier | Iters | Time (MacBook) | PLY size | Use case |
|------|-------|----------------|----------|----------|
| Preview | 7k | ~45 min | 30-90MB | Quick check |
| Standard | 15k | ~2 hr | 80-160MB | Customer delivery |
| Premium | 30k | ~4 hr | 150-400MB | Hero specimens |

### Hardware Nodes
| Node | Machine | RAM | Status | Notes |
|------|---------|-----|--------|-------|
| Mama | Mac Studio M1 | 32GB | Active | MPS crashes on dense clouds |
| MacBook | M4 Max | 36GB | Active | Primary development |
| GUS | M4 Mini | 24GB | Active | Overflow only |

**Routing:** Mama -> MacBook -> GUS (never default to GUS)

### Current Specimens
| ID | Mineral | Grade | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| cupr-001 | Cuprite on Copper | A (89) | LIVE ($3,200) |
| azur-001 | Azurite | D | Review pending |
| chry-001 | Chrysocolla | F | SKIP (specular) |
| amet-001 | Amethyst | C (61) | RESHOOT |
| boris-001 to 012 | TBD | — | Gem show (scheduled) |

### Key Rules
- COLMAP runs on raw `images_jpg/` ONLY — never rembg/processed
- Always use `run-splat.sh` — never call opensplat directly
- Never hardcode opensplat path (use detection loop)
- `--cpu` fallback = 14hr vs 1.5hr. Fail loud on MPS crash, never silently degrade
- Each run gets a unique dated directory — no overwrites
- `opensplat.log` MUST be co-located with output.ply (required for scoring)

### PLY Deployment
```bash
# Manual only (Director-gated):
SPECIMEN_ID=cupr-001 deploy-splat.sh ~/path/to/output.ply
# Uploads to Vercel Blob, updates splatUrl in specimen data, git pushes
```

### Upload Script
`scripts/upload-splats.mjs` converts PLY -> KSPLAT and uploads to Vercel Blob storage.

---

## API Routes

### POST /api/checkout
Creates Stripe Checkout session. Validates availability, price threshold ($5K+), specimen existence.
Shipping: Domestic Standard ($45), Priority ($75), International ($125), Local Pickup (free).

### POST /api/webhooks/stripe
Handles `checkout.session.completed` (marks sold in Sheet), `payment_intent.payment_failed`.

### POST /api/revalidate
ISR revalidation trigger. Requires `x-revalidate-secret` header. Called by Google Apps Script on sheet edit.

---

## Google Sheets Integration

**Sheet columns:** ID, Name, Mineral, Locality, CrystalSystem, Dimensions, Weight, Price, Availability, Description, PhotoIds, Notes, PublishStatus

**Key functions in `src/lib/google-sheets.ts`:**
- `fetchAllSpecimens()` — All specimens (cached)
- `fetchSpecimens()` — Published only
- `fetchSpecimenById(id)` — Single specimen
- `markSpecimensAsSold(ids)` — Patch availability on purchase

**Images:** Google Drive `https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/{fileId}` or local `/images/specimens/{id}.jpg`

---

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY | Yes | Full JSON service account (stringified) |
| GOOGLE_SHEET_ID | Yes | Sheet ID from URL |
| REVALIDATE_SECRET | Yes | Shared secret for ISR webhook |
| STRIPE_SECRET_KEY | Checkout | sk_test_ or sk_live_ |
| STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY | Checkout | pk_test_ or pk_live_ |
| STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET | Webhooks | whsec_ from Stripe |

---

## Style Guide

- **Fonts:** Cormorant Garamond (headings/display), Montserrat (body)
- **Palette:** Silver/platinum accent, amber crystal highlights, dark backgrounds
- **Animations:** shimmer, float, fade-out (defined in tailwind.config.ts)
- **Design:** Museum/gallery aesthetic. Clean, professional, not flashy
- **Map:** Pure SVG + React useState for mine localities (no Leaflet/Mapbox)

---

## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. **Stripe isolation** — Borussia Stripe keys NEVER appear in other projects
2. **Client data isolation** — Customer PII stays in Borussia handlers only
3. **File vs directory collision** — Before creating `src/data/foo.ts`, check if `src/data/foo/` exists
4. **Content edits** — Edit `src/data/` files. Don't touch `src/app/`, `src/components/`, `src/lib/` for content changes
5. **Splat pipeline** — Raw images only for COLMAP. Always use run-splat.sh
6. **No TODO comments** — Complete the work or don't start it

